<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-09-10T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-09-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="429" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d429">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">763.72/2140½</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Wilson</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-09-10">
                                    <hi rend="italic">10 September, 1915</hi>.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: I do not think any
                            answer to this despatch is necessary.<note n="54" xml:id="d429fn1">See
                                footnote 52, <ref target="#pg_476">p. 476</ref>.</note>
                        </p>
                        <p>It is no doubt useful to know what opinion is on the other side of the
                            water. After while even Englishmen will begin to understand (I wonder if
                            they really ever will?) that what we are guided by is our sense of what
                            is just and right and not our sensibility as regards what other nations
                            think about us.</p>
                        <p>Faithfully Yours,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>W. W.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>